Claims CLAIMS: We Claim: 1. A method, comprising: fusion welding a an aluminum alloy composition to an aluminum component, wherein the aluminum component comprises a 7xxx series aluminum alloy, and wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises an aluminum alloy, in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up 0.15% Fe; from 2.75% to 3.25% Cu; from 2.4% to 2.9% Mg; from 5.4% to 5.9% Zn; from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; up to 0.9% Ti; and up to 0.3% B. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises 2.85 to 3.25 wt. % Cu. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises 2.5 to 2.9 wt% Mg. 4. The method of claim 1, wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises 5.5 to 5.9 wt% Zn. 5. A method, comprising: fusion welding an aluminum alloy composition to an aluminum component, wherein the aluminum component comprises a 7xxx series aluminum alloy, and wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises an aluminum alloy, in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up to 0.15% Fe; from 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; 

 from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn; from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; up to 0.9% Ti; and up to 0.3% B. 6. A product, comprising: a first aluminum component, wherein the first aluminum component comprises a 7xxx series alloy; a second aluminum component; and a weld attaching the first aluminum component to the second aluminum component, wherein the weld is formed from an aluminum alloy composition, and wherein the aluminum alloy composition is an aluminum alloy comprising in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up to 0.15% Fe; from 2.75% to 3.25% Cu; from 2.4% to 2.9% Mg; from 5.4% to 5.9% Zn; from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; up to 0.9%Ti; and up to 0.3% B. 7. The product of claim 6, wherein the second aluminum component comprises one of a 7xxx aluminum alloy, a 2xxx series alloy or a 5xxx series alloy. 8. A product, comprising: a first aluminum component, wherein the first aluminum component comprises a 7xxx series alloy; a second aluminum component; and a weld attaching the first aluminum component to the second aluminum component, wherein the weld is formed from an aluminum alloy composition, and wherein the aluminum alloy composition is an aluminum alloy comprising in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up to 0.15% Fe; 

 from 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn; from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; up to 0.9% Ti; and up to 0.3% B . 9. The product of claim 8, wherein the second aluminum component comprises one of a 7xxx aluminum alloy, a 2xxx series alloy or a 5xxx series alloy. 10. A method of making an additively manufactured product, comprising: (a) selectively heating at least a portion of an aluminum alloy composition to a temperature above a liquidus temperature of the aluminum alloy composition, thereby forming a molten pool, wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises an aluminum alloy, in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up to 0.15% Fe; from 2.75% to 3.25% Cu; from 2.4% to 2.9% Mg; from 5.4% to 5.9% Zn; and from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; (b) cooling the molten pool thereby forming a solidified mass; and (c) repeating (a)-(b), thereby producing the additively manufactured product. 11. The method of claim 10, wherein the additively manufactured product is free of cracking. 12. The method of claim 10, wherein the aluminum alloy composition is configured as a wire. 13. The method of claim 10, wherein the aluminum alloy composition is configured as a powder. 14. A method of making an additively manufactured product, comprising: (a) selectively heating at least a portion of an aluminum alloy composition to a temperature above a liquidus temperature of the aluminum alloy composition, thereby forming a molten 

 pool, wherein the aluminum alloy composition comprises an aluminum alloy, in weight percent: up to 0.15% Si; up to 0.15% Fe; from 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn; and from 0.10% to 0.12% Zr; (b) cooling the molten pool thereby forming a solidified mass; and (c) repeating (a)-(b), thereby producing the additively manufactured product. 15. The method of claim 14, wherein the additively manufactured product is free of cracking. 16. The method of claim 14, wherein the aluminum alloy composition is configured as a wire. 17. The method of claim 14, wherein the aluminum alloy composition is configured as a powder. 18. An aluminum alloy product, comprising: from 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; and from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn, the balance being aluminum, incidental elements and impurities. 19. An aluminum alloy product, comprising: from 2.75% to 3.25% Cu; from 2.4% to 2.9% Mg; from 5.4% to 5.9% Zn, the balance being aluminum, incidental elements and impurities. 20. An aluminum alloy composition, comprising: 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; and from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn, 

 the balance being aluminum, incidental elements and impurities. An aluminum alloy composition, comprising: 5.5% to 6.0% Cu; from 1.4% to 1.9% Mg; and from 2.9% to 3.4% Zn, the balance being aluminum, incidental elements and impurities.
